com%2Fworld-news%2Fabandoned-as-child-chinese-woman-builds-fashion-brand-worth-36-million-11156908%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Huang%20eventually%20saw%20a%20chance%20in%20China's%20expanding%20e-commerce%20industry%20after%20years%20of%20hardship%20and%20even%20unsuccessful%20business%20ventures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fabandoned-as-child-chinese-woman-builds-fashion-brand-worth-36-million-11156908%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amazon's%20%2450%20billion%20OpenAI%20deal%20keeps%20the%20cloud%20giant%20firmly%20in%20the%20AI%20race.%20Here's%20what%20it%20means.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6900fcb9599d46a4ccc0ff6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%3Cp%3ENoah%20Berger%2FNoah%20Berger%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20invests%20%2450%20billion%20in%20OpenAI%2C%20boosting%20its%20position%20in%20the%20AI%20industry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20OpenAI%20partnership%20enhances%20AWS's%20Bedrock%20services.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon's%20Trainium%20chips%20gain%20momentum%20as%20OpenAI%20makes%20large%20commitment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ai-spending-plan-capex-stuns-wall-street-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20making%20its%20boldest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-aws-cloud-customers-proserve-consulting-fees-ai-automates-work-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20move%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20agreed%20to%20invest%20%2450%20billion%20in%20OpenAI%20as%20part%20of%20the%20startup's%20record%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-amazon-nvidia-microsoft-everyone-against-google-ai-dominance-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%24110%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20fundraising%20round%2C%20which%20values%20the%20ChatGPT%20maker%20at%20%24840%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20multi-year%20partnership%20includes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%2415%20billion%20will%20be%20invested%20upfront%2C%20with%20another%20%2435%20billion%20to%20follow%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20once%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20conditions%26quot%3B%20are%20met.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECo-creation%20of%20new%20AI%20system%20architecture%20powered%20by%20OpenAI%20models%20and%20available%20on%20Amazon%20Bedrock.%20It%20enables%20developers%20to%20retain%20memory%20and%20context%20over%20time%20and%20deploy%20more%20advanced%20AI%20applications.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20Web%20Services%20will%20become%20the%20exclusive%20third-party%20cloud%20distribution%20provider%20for%20OpenAI's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-fidji-simo-software-frontier-enterprise-ai-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFrontier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20platform%20for%20managing%20AI%20agents%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20expands%20its%20existing%20AWS%20cloud%20agreement%20by%20%24100%20billion%20over%208%20years%20and%20commits%20to%20using%202%20gigawatts%20of%20AWS%20Trainium%20chips%2C%20including%20future%20generations%20of%20the%20AI%20chip.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20will%20help%20build%20customized%20AI%20models%20for%20Amazon's%20consumer%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20eye-popping%20valuation%2C%20the%20deal%20cements%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%20as%20a%20core%20infrastructure%20partner%20to%20OpenAI%20and%20positions%20the%20cloud%20giant%20squarely%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20escalating%20AI%20arms%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%203%20biggest%20takeaways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b8423b96-581e-4f79-8781-10cad253e0e9%5C%22%3E1.%20AWS%20closes%20the%20AI%20perception%20gap%20and%20counters%20Microsoft%20and%20Google%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20much%20of%20the%20past%203%20years%2C%20Microsoft%20has%20been%20seen%20as%20an%20early%20winner%20in%20generative%20AI%2C%20thanks%20to%20its%20deep%20partnership%20with%20OpenAI.%20Google%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20leaned%20on%20its%20in-house%20Gemini%20models%20and%20AI%20research%20strength%20to%20gain%20new%20cloud%20business%20and%20AI%20users.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ai-startups-delaying-aws-spending-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eperceived%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20step%20behind%20by%20some%20analysts%20and%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriday's%20deal%20potentially%20changes%20that%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20important%20strategic%20move%20that%20keeps%20them%20in%20the%20AI%20race%2C%26quot%3B%20DA%20Davidson%20analyst%20Gil%20Luria%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombined%20with%20its%20multibillion-dollar%20investment%20in%20Anthropic%2C%20Amazon%20now%20holds%20meaningful%20partnerships%20with%20the%20top%20two%20independent%20AI%20labs%2C%20creating%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-amazon-nvidia-microsoft-everyone-against-google-ai-dominance-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecounterweight%20to%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20reducing%20reliance%20on%20any%20single%20model%20provider%2C%20Luria%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBNP%20analysts%20noted%20that%20Microsoft%20investors%20will%20be%20closely%20watching%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20OpenAI%20continues%20to%20partner%20with%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20becoming%20the%20exclusive%20third-party%20infrastructure%20provider%20for%20OpenAI's%20Frontier%20platform%2C%20AWS%20is%20now%20positioned%20as%20a%20core%20backbone%20for%20enterprise%20AI%20and%20autonomous%20agent%20development.%20While%20Microsoft%20retains%20certain%20API%20exclusivity%20for%20OpenAI%20models%2C%20AWS's%20Frontier%20deal%20gives%20it%20a%20meaningful%20foothold%20in%20OpenAI's%20most%20advanced%20offerings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGartner%20analyst%20Jason%20Wong%20called%20the%20move%20a%20%26quot%3Bmajor%20coup%26quot%3B%20for%20AWS%2C%20noting%20significant%20customer%20interest%20in%20Frontier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpenAI%20gives%20them%20a%20lot%20of%20market%20traction%20with%20enterprises%20to%20build%20their%20agentic%20solutions%20on%20AWS%2C%26quot%3B%20Wong%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d275873-0e89-45a9-91c2-d0cabb1a5c90%5C%22%3E2.%20A%20potential%20threat%20to%20Anthropic%20and%20a%20major%20boost%20for%20Bedrock%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20deepening%20relationship%20with%20OpenAI%20inevitably%20raises%20questions%20about%20Anthropic%2C%20the%20AI%20startup%20behind%20Claude%20in%20which%20Amazon%20has%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ai-bet-anthropic-soars-61-billion-valuation-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvested%3C%2Fa%3E%20heavily.%20Anthropic%20remains%20a%20key%20AWS%20partner%2C%20but%20the%20new%20OpenAI%20partnership%20introduces%20competitive%20tension.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20Bedrock%2C%20which%20offers%20access%20to%20other%20AI%20models%2C%20stands%20to%20benefit%20significantly.%20Adding%20OpenAI%20models%20to%20Bedrock%20through%20Friday's%20deal%20will%20give%20developers%20more%20options%20and%20could%20make%20AWS%20a%20more%20compelling%20one-stop%20shop%20for%20enterprise%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJefferies%20analyst%20Brent%20Thill%20framed%20the%20move%20as%20an%20expansion%20of%20choice.%20He%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20developers%20will%20be%20excited%20to%20have%20OpenAI%20Frontier%20available%20to%20build%20more%20advanced%20applications.%20For%20OpenAI%2C%20access%20to%20the%20world's%20largest%20cloud%20provider%20by%20market%20share%20unlocks%20massive%20enterprise%20distribution%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20could%20complicate%20Amazon's%20relationship%20with%20Anthropic.%20Bedrock%20has%20been%20a%20major%20distribution%20channel%20for%20Anthropic's%20models%2C%20but%20adding%20OpenAI's%20lineup%20may%20dilute%20that%20advantage%20and%20redirect%20some%20enterprise%20AI%20workloads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bfb5cc63-818c-493f-8129-b08d7b630f02%5C%22%3E3.%20A%20stamp%20of%20approval%20for%20Trainium%2C%20Amazon's%20custom%20silicon%20bet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20consequential%20element%20of%20the%20partnership%20is%20hardware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20deal%2C%20OpenAI%20has%20committed%20to%20deploy%202%20gigawatts%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-amazon-ai-chips-less-competitive-nvidia-gpus-trainium-aws-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrainium%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Amazon's%20in-house%20AI%20chip.%20For%20years%2C%20AWS%20has%20invested%20heavily%20in%20custom%20silicon%20to%20differentiate%20from%20rivals%20and%20reduce%20its%20dependence%20on%20Nvidia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20firm%20William%20Blair%20said%20the%20commitment%20serves%20as%20%26quot%3Banother%20big%20vote%20of%20confidence%26quot%3B%20for%20Amazon's%20custom%20chip%20strategy%2C%20noting%20Anthropic%20is%20also%20a%20heavy%20Trainium%20user.%20More%20Trainium%20deployment%20also%20drives%20deeper%20integration%20between%20OpenAI's%20software%20stack%20and%20AWS%20infrastructure%2C%20potentially%20locking%20in%20long-term%20demand%20for%20Amazon's%20chips%20and%20cloud%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20clearly%20demand%20for%20AWS%2C%20and%20our%20sense%20is%20that%20AWS%20revenue%20growth%20is%20only%20going%20to%20be%20limited%20by%20how%20much%20compute%20capacity%20AWS%20can%20bring%20online%2C%26quot%3B%20William%20Blair%20analysts%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aekim%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eekim%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%2C%20Telegram%2C%20or%20WhatsApp%20at%20650-942-3061.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-openai-deal-cloud-ai-race-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772452802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F697a98add3c7faef0ecd2315%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-openai-deal-cloud-ai-race-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20deal%20strengthens%20AWS's%20AI%20offerings%20and%20may%20help%20fend%20off%20challenges%20from%20cloud%20rivals%20Microsoft%20and%20Google.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ekim%40businessinsider.com%20(Eugene%20Kim)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-openai-deal-cloud-ai-race-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20new%20report%20reveals%20that%20a%20third%20of%20colon%20cancer%20cases%20now%20occur%20in%20the%20rectum.%20Take%20these%20steps%20to%20protect%20yourself%20at%20any%20age.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225604%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22woman%20on%20the%20toilet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a0e712d3e2f1aef369a1a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223736%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3Eherstockart%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERectal%20cancer%2C%20a%20form%20of%20colon%20cancer%20that%20often%20comes%20with%20more%20blood%20in%20stool%2C%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20suspect%20something%20in%20our%20environment%20is%20triggering%20this%20%E2%80%94%20diet%20changes%20may%20play%20a%20role.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAt-home%20stool%20tests%2C%20colonoscopies%2C%20and%20more%20awareness%20of%20key%20symptoms%20can%20all%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-so-many-young-people-getting-colon-cancer-answer-infancy-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20cases%20are%20being%20diagnosed%20in%20the%20rectums%20of%20people%20in%20their%2040s%2C%2050s%2C%20and%2060s%2C%20a%20clear%20sign%20that%20something%20in%20our%20modern%20environment%20is%20perturbing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecolon%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20making%20colon%20cancer%20more%20common%20in%20younger%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.3322%2Fcaac.70067%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20today%20from%20the%20American%20Cancer%20Society%20shows%20that%20colon%20cancer%20is%20becoming%20a%20disease%20of%20middle%20age%2C%20hitting%20people%20in%20the%20prime%20of%20their%20life%2C%20when%20they're%20buying%20homes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-cancer-work-career-impact-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egrowing%20careers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20building%20families.%20In%20particular%2C%20rectal%20cancers%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20colon%20cancer%20located%20at%20the%20very%20tail%20end%20of%20the%20intestinal%20tract%2C%20are%20skyrocketing%2C%20now%20accounting%20for%20one-third%20of%20all%20colon%20cancers%20diagnosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20aren't%20exactly%20sure%20why%20this%20is%20happening%2C%20but%20the%20data%20is%20striking%3A%20the%20rate%20of%20rectal%20cancers%20diagnosed%20in%20people%20under%2050%20doubled%20in%20the%2024-year%20period%20from%201998%20to%202022.%20That's%20an%20indication%20that%20whatever%20is%20driving%20the%20rise%20of%20young%20colon%20cancer%20is%20having%20more%20of%20an%20impact%20specifically%20on%20the%20tissues%20in%20people's%20rectums%2C%20suggesting%20an%20environmental%20trigger%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20lack%20of%20physical%20activity%2C%20could%20be%20to%20blame%20for%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20some%20either%20environmental%20or%20behavioral%20exposure%20that%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20last%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%26quot%3B%20cancer%20epidemiologist%20Rebecca%20Siegel%2C%20first%20author%20of%20the%20new%20report%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhatever%20this%20change%20in%20exposure%20was%2C%20it's%20having%20a%20much%20larger%20influence%20on%20cancer%20development%20in%20the%20rectum.%20It's%20a%20really%20important%20clue%20for%20researchers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278738dca-c581-43ac-b4ed-c0a1c85b57c3%5C%22%3EThis%20isn't%20your%20grandfather's%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226968%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22colon%20cancer%20flags%20on%20national%20mall%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a1e3a31fb3fcb426489e1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EColorectal%20cancer%20has%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20people%20under%2050%2C%20and%20experts%20now%20recommend%20colonoscopies%20to%20everyone%20starting%20at%20age%2045.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Morigi%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Fight%20Colorectal%20Cancer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EColon%20cancer%20has%20quickly%20become%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edeadliest%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20people%20under%2050%2C%20but%20researchers%20don't%20yet%20know%20why.%20The%20news%20that%20rectal%20cancer%20is%20driving%20the%20trend%20is%20useful%20for%20researchers%20because%20different%20triggers%20impact%20different%20areas%20of%20the%20gut.%20Physical%20inactivity%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20a%20key%20driver%20of%20some%20colon%20cancers%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20the%20rectal%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20thought%20that%20it%20is%20something%2C%20maybe%2C%20that%20we're%20eating%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%2C%20who%20is%20the%20senior%20scientific%20director%20of%20surveillance%20research%20at%20the%20American%20Cancer%20Society%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BPartly%20because%20that's%20the%20big%20exposure%20for%20the%20colon%2C%20but%20also%20because%20that%20is%20something%20that%20has%20changed%20dramatically%20since%201950.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20with%20the%20Baby%20Boomers%2C%20every%20successive%20generation%20now%20has%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20developing%20colon%20cancer.%20You%20can%20see%20this%20in%20the%20data%3A%20Colon%20cancer%20rates%20are%20rising%203%25%20per%20year%20in%20people%20under%2050%2C%20and%20most%20of%20them%20are%20being%20diagnosed%20at%20an%20advanced%20stage%2C%20whereas%20colon%20cancer%20rates%20are%20decreasing%20in%20people%20over%2065%2C%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20about%202.5%25%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20new%20report%2C%20almost%20half%20(45%25)%20of%20colon%20cancer%20diagnoses%20today%20are%20in%20people%20under%2065.%20The%20face%20of%20colon%20cancer%20is%20changing%2C%20and%20both%20experts%20and%20patients%20are%20clamoring%20for%20more%20recognition%20and%20awareness.%20Though%20lifestyle%20moves%20like%20eating%20a%20healthy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchef-grew-up-mediterranean-diet-tricks-add-fiber-meals-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efiber-rich%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20getting%20regular%20movement%2C%20avoiding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprocessed-meat-increases-cancer-risk-what-to-know-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20meats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20skipping%20binge%20drinking%20can%20all%20help%20lower%20your%20risk%20of%20developing%20colon%20cancer%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20guarantee.%20Plenty%20of%20people%20with%20clean%20diets%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalcium-lower-colorectal-colon-cancer-risk-foods-contain-high-in-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehealthy%20habits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20no%20family%20history%20of%20colon%20cancer%20are%20getting%20diagnosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20like%20a%20slow-moving%20tsunami%20where%20it's%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20affect%20more%20and%20more%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226989339c-ce67-47ea-8ed6-2a9b757bef1d%5C%22%3EThe%20trend%20is%20global%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20just%20happening%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it's%20a%20trend%20that's%20progressively%20being%20mirrored%20across%20the%20globe.%20At%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-colon-cancer-on-the-rise-reasons-why-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E26%20other%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20reported%20similar%20trends%20in%20young%20adults%20under%2050%20developing%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-people-cancer-crisis-risk-tips-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EYoung%20colon%20cancer%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20getting%20diagnosed%20later%2C%20and%20it's%20deadlier%20too.%20Today%2C%20three-quarters%20of%20colon%20cancer%20diagnoses%20in%20patients%20under%2050%20are%20advanced%20disease%2C%20and%20one-third%20of%20the%20estimated%2055%2C230%20colon%20cancer%20deaths%20this%20year%20in%20the%20US%20will%20be%20in%20people%20under%2065.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22139fad03-9507-4073-915c-4d642dc015d5%5C%22%3EBloody%20stool%20is%20a%20warning%20sign%20that%20doctors%20and%20patients%20need%20to%20take%20seriously%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22doctor%20in%20coat%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a1dbced3e2f1aef369af8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExperts%20say%20don't%20shy%20away%20from%20poop%20talk%20with%20your%20doctor.%3Cp%3Ebymuratdeniz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20awareness%20on%20the%20part%20of%20patients%20and%20doctors%2C%20as%20well%20as%20more%20colonoscopies%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20not%20only%20detect%20cancer%2C%20but%20also%20prevent%20it%20through%20the%20removal%20of%20precancerous%20growths%20%E2%80%94%20are%20needed%20to%20reverse%20the%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20an%20opportunity%20for%20earlier%20diagnosis%2C%20but%20the%20problem%20is%2C%20especially%20for%20younger%20people%2C%20they're%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20symptoms%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20symptoms%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20sometimes%20they%20even%20do%20go%20to%20the%20doctor%20with%20these%20symptoms%2C%20and%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-thought-she-had-hemorrhoids-was-diagnosed-colon-cancer-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ediagnosed%20with%20hemorrhoids%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaura%20Behnke%2C%20who%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20late-stage%20colon%20cancer%20at%20age%2042%2C%20just%20a%20few%20months%20after%20giving%20birth%20to%20her%20baby%20girl%2C%20is%20one%20of%20those%20patients%20who%20assumed%20the%20bloody%20mucus%20attached%20to%20her%20stool%20was%20probably%20just%20pregnancy%20hemorrhoids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20at%20any%20point%20asked%20me%20'What's%20the%20bleeding%20like%3F%20How%20often%20is%20it%20happening%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20just%20said%2C%20'Oh%2C%20hemorrhoids%2C%20cool.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Behnke%20and%20Siegel%20emphasized%20that%20normalizing%20talk%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frectal-bleeding-most-common-early-sign-of-colon-cancer-taboo-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esymptoms%20like%20bloody%20stool%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20stomach%20cramping%20are%20critical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20important%20for%20people%20to%20have%20these%20conversations%20with%20their%20family%20at%20the%20dinner%20table%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%20%26quot%3BChange%20the%20topic%2C%20normalize%20this%20kind%20of%20talk%2C%20because%20that'll%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%2C%20too%2C%20are%20slowly%20gaining%20recognition%20that%20younger%20patients%20can%20get%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20over%20age%2045%20should%20be%20going%20in%20for%20regular%20colonoscopies.%20If%20a%20colonoscopy%20feels%20too%20inconvenient%2C%20start%20with%20a%20simple%20and%20cheap%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feasy-at-home-colon-cancer-screening-tests-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehome%20stool%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20called%20a%20fecal%20immunochemical%20test%20(FIT).%20The%20test%20is%20very%20good%20at%20detecting%20rectal%20cancers.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F33562775%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2021%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Germany%2C%20which%20assessed%20how%20well%20nine%20different%20brands%20of%20home%20FIT%20tests%20work%20at%20picking%20up%20colon%20cancer%2C%20found%20that%20across%20the%20board%2C%20FIT%20tests%20have%20the%20highest%20sensitivity%20for%20rectal%20tumors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20number%20one%20thing%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-misdiagnosis-young-people-ibs-gluten-allergy-symptoms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20symptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20bloody%20mucus%20in%20your%20stool%2C%20severe%20abdominal%20cramping%2C%20or%20other%20changes%20in%20your%20bathroom%20habits%20are%20worth%20going%20over%20with%20a%20doctor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20is%20pretty%20clear%20now%2C%20hopefully%20becoming%20more%20clear%20to%20everyone%20that%20this%20is%20not%20an%20old%20man's%20disease%2C%26quot%3B%20Behnke%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20if%20you%20do%20have%20any%20sort%20of%20symptoms%2C%20any%20sort%20of%20concerns%2C%20anything%20that%20doesn't%20feel%20right%2C%20you%20have%20every%20right%20to%20go%20ask%20a%20doctor%20about%20it%20and%20to%20demand%20some%20answers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-rectal-cancer-rise-young-people-protect-yourself-lower-risk-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772452801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a0e6cdfd4fbd083f2929a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-rectal-cancer-rise-young-people-protect-yourself-lower-risk-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Colon%20cancer%20is%20now%20the%20deadliest%20cancer%20for%20people%20under%2050%2C%20and%20researchers%20are%20scrambling%20to%20understand%20why%20rectal%20cases%20are%20driving%20the%20trend.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbrueck%40businessinsider.com%20(Hilary%20Brueck)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider