20if%20they%20love%20the%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Frobert-pasin%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobert%20Pasin%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20CEO%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.radioflyer.com%2Fpages%2Fradio-flyer-history%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERadio%20Flyer%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20business%2C%20Radio%20Flyer%2C%20is%20in%20its%20109th%20year%20of%20operation%2C%20and%20it%20has%20only%20had%20three%20CEOs%3A%20my%20grandfather%2C%20my%20dad%2C%20and%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20grandfather%20was%20a%20charismatic%2C%20energetic%20guy.%20He%20immigrated%20from%20Italy%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoys-in-the-national-toy-hall-of-fame-2016-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efounded%20Radio%20Flyer%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20one-room%20workshop%20on%20Chicago's%20West%20Side.%20My%20dad%20was%20his%20only%20son%20and%20took%20over%20the%20company%20out%20of%20a%20sense%20of%20obligation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20would%20have%20been%20in%20leadership%20if%20it%20weren't%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-at-my-mothers-business-alongside-sister-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efamily%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20did%20some%20good%20things%2C%20like%20protecting%20the%20company's%20intellectual%20property%20in%20a%20way%20that%20hadn't%20been%20done%20before.%20But%20he%20didn't%20enjoy%20managing%20people%20or%20running%20a%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e84e2b58-4c5d-48ba-8ac4-bfcbcd2e3f0c%5C%22%3EI%20was%20the%20only%20sibling%20interested%20in%20taking%20over%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pendulum%20swings%20in%20families%2C%20and%20I%20shared%20my%20grandfather's%20passion%20for%20Radio%20Flyer.%20I%20remember%20being%205%20years%20old%2C%20holding%20my%20dad's%20hand%2C%20watching%20red%20wagon%20after%20red%20wagon%20come%20down%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-mile-long-factory-where-f-35-stealth-fighters-made-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eassembly%20line%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20felt%20magical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221371%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20working%20in%20old%20factory%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699ccb032237a6a8f0cdb232%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22977%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobert%20Pasin's%20grandfather%2C%20Antonio%20Pasin%2C%20founded%20Radio%20Flyer.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Robert%20Pasin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20in%20the%20factory%20during%20high%20school%20and%20college%2C%20doing%20mundane%20jobs%20like%20packing%20and%20loading.%20I%20even%20enjoyed%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20my%20dad's%20experience%2C%20he%20never%20pressured%20my%20siblings%20or%20me%20to%20be%20involved%20with%20the%20company.%20I'm%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrities-who-are-the-youngest-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyoungest%20of%20the%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20was%20the%20most%20interested%20in%20the%20business%2C%20so%20the%20succession%20unfolded%20pretty%20naturally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2227931aa3-1861-40bf-b196-5444f1909616%5C%22%3EMy%20dad%20was%20relieved%20when%20I%20took%20over%20at%2028%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20working%20full-time%20at%20Radio%20Flyer%20in%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20the%20company%20was%20in%20crisis%20because%20of%20my%20dad's%20ambivalent%20leadership.%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20big%20ideas%3B%20I%20was%20just%20focused%20on%20solving%20problem%20after%20problem.%20When%20I%20did%2C%20I%20could%20see%20the%20relief%20on%20my%20dad's%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222228%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robert%20Pasin%20with%20dad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699cccd6156648bc16a8c1bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221416%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobert%20Pasin%20says%20his%20dad%20was%20relieved%20when%20he%20took%20over%20the%20company.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Robert%20Pasin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20our%20business%20differences%2C%20my%20dad%20and%20I%20had%20a%20great%20relationship%20and%20lots%20of%20trust.%20I%20was%20extremely%20respectful%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20was%20still%20the%20boss%3B%20in%20return%2C%20he%20gave%20me%20free%20rein%20to%20make%20decisions.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20typical%20situation%20where%20the%20old%20guy%20wouldn't%20let%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%2028%20when%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudy-younger-ceos-more-likely-to-embrace-remote-work-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eofficially%20became%20the%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20was%20fired%20up%20about%20the%20company%2C%20so%20being%20at%20the%20helm%20felt%20invigorating.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20there%20were%20nights%20when%20I%20was%20up%20late%2C%20worrying%20that%20we%20were%20going%20to%20go%20out%20of%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb2c3deb-fb77-4beb-9063-8ed6a779d642%5C%22%3EI%20capitalized%20on%20the%20nostalgia%20customers%20felt%20toward%20the%20brand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERadio%20Flyer%20had%20become%20too%20inward-oriented.%20We%20weren't%20in%20touch%20with%20customers%2C%20and%20when%20competitors%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrollers-are-overrated-wagons-are-better-parent-of-3-kids-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereleased%20plastic%20wagons%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20were%20totally%20caught%20off%20guard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20asking%20people%20their%20thoughts%20on%20Radio%20Flyer.%20To%20my%20family%2C%20Radio%20Flyer%20had%20been%20a%20very%20material%20company%3A%20wood-and-steel%20wagons%20made%20in%20Chicago.%20But%20customers%20told%20me%20about%20pretending%20their%20wagon%20was%20a%20car%2C%20and%20racing%20down%20the%20streets%20with%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%2C%20for%20customers%2C%20the%20brand%20represented%20free%20time%20and%20imagination%2C%20being%20outside%20with%20the%20wind%20in%20their%20hair.%20We%20had%20this%20goldmine%20reputation%20that%20we%20hadn't%20tapped%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20that%20allowed%20me%20to%20expand%20beyond%20just%20wagons%20into%20other%20products%20that%20tapped%20into%20that%20same%20nostalgia%20and%20playfulness.%20My%20wife%20and%20I%20were%20raising%20four%20kids%2C%20so%20we%20knew%20what%20they%20loved%20and%20what%20made%20life%20easier%20for%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22854d153a-f1ef-470e-96ef-75780cd9d948%5C%22%3EI%20only%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20work%20here%20if%20they%20love%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20kids%20loved%20coming%20to%20work%20with%20me%20because%20there%20were%20always%20fun%20wagons%20or%20trikes%20for%20them%20to%20play%20with.%20Even%20now%2C%20Radio%20Flyer%20has%20a%20great%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftake-your-child-to-work-day-founder-advice-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBring%20Your%20Kid%20to%20Work%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20Day%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20we%20began%20having%20annual%20family%20meetings%20about%20the%20business.%20It's%20a%20facilitated%20meeting%20run%20by%20a%20consulting%20group%2C%20where%20me%2C%20my%20wife%2C%20and%20our%20children%20all%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20talk%20about%20anything%20on%20our%20minds%20with%20relation%20to%20the%20business%2C%20or%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20my%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20who%20range%20in%20age%20from%2017%20to%2030%20%E2%80%94%20to%20understand%20that%20they're%20welcome%20in%20the%20business%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20pressure%20to%20join.%20Since%20Radio%20Flyer%20is%20a%20household%20name%2C%20people%20often%20assume%20they'll%20work%20here%2C%20but%20so%20far%2C%20none%20of%20them%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20fine%20with%20me.%20I've%20encouraged%20them%20to%20gain%20work%20experience%20elsewhere%20and%20to%20join%20Radio%20Flyer%20only%20if%20they%20really%20love%20the%20work.%20I%20tell%20them%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20not%20a%20good%20match%2C%20the%20business%20is%20going%20to%20ruin%20you%2C%20and%20you'll%20ruin%20the%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c1c7806-ab79-440d-b3dd-c29c1d5f04f0%5C%22%3EI%20wish%20my%20grandfather%20could%20see%20the%20business%20he%20started%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20grandfather%20died%20when%20I%20was%2021%2C%20and%20before%20that%2C%20he%20had%20dementia.%20I%20never%20got%20to%20talk%20to%20him%20about%20the%20business%20we%20both%20love.%20If%20I%20could%20talk%20to%20anyone%2C%20living%20or%20dead%2C%20it%20would%20be%20him.%20I'd%20like%20to%20show%20him%20around%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20think%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222496%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Family%20photo%20grandfather%20holding%20baby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699ccddfefb52c8bd0deb7ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223520%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobert%20Pasin's%20grandfather%20never%20saw%20him%20take%20over%20the%20company.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Robert%20Pasin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20a%20fourth%20generation%20of%20the%20family%20comes%20to%20Radio%20Flyer%2C%20I%20want%20the%20company's%20legacy%20to%20be%20its%20good%20work.%20I'm%20proud%20that%20my%20family%20has%20helped%20bring%20the%20world%20out%20to%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fradio-flyer-109-year-family-business-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20