C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eride-hailing%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20riders%20negotiate%20ride%20prices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20operates%20in%2048%20countries%20and%20was%20the%20second-most-downloaded%20ride-hailing%20app%20in%202025.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExecutives%20explained%20InDrive's%20growth%20plans%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why%20it%20pulled%20out%20of%20the%20US%20last%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriven-for-uber-decade-dont-know-what-my-future-holds-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eride-hailing%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%20InDrive%2C%20riders%20and%20drivers%20have%20to%20do%20something%20many%20Uber%20users%20have%20never%20done%3A%20negotiate%20the%20price%20of%20a%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20accepting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frideshare-drivers-wages-robotaxi-markets-data-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrip%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%20set%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eby%20the%20app%2C%20passengers%20can%20submit%20their%20ride%20request%20along%20with%20a%20proposed%20payment%20amount.%20Drivers%20can%20then%20view%20the%20proposal%20and%20accept%20it%20or%20send%20a%20counteroffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20final%20decision%20is%20yours%2C%26quot%3B%20Evgenia%20Matrosova%2C%20InDrive's%20chief%20ride-hailing%20officer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInDrive%20said%20it%20takes%20a%20commission%20of%20about%2010%25%20on%20each%20ride.%20By%20comparison%2C%20Uber%20hasn't%20disclosed%20how%20much%20it%20takes%20from%20each%20ride%2C%20but%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-uber-upfront-pricing-could-be-key-to-business-turnaround-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20driver%20trip%20data%20suggested%20it%20averaged%2042%25%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInDrive's%20model%20differs%20from%20other%20major%20gig%20work%20apps.%20On%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20drivers%20see%20a%20fare%20for%20a%20potential%20trip%2C%20which%20they%20can%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaccept%20or%20reject.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOn%20Uber%2C%20that%20payout%20can%20vary%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-uber-upfront-pricing-could-be-key-to-business-turnaround-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUber's%20upfront%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%20strategy%2C%20which%20uses%20algorithms%20to%20set%20prices%20and%20payouts%20%E2%80%94%20and%20doesn't%20give%20riders%20or%20drivers%20the%20option%20to%20suggest%20other%20amounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e52d7fb9-910a-404e-927f-744cb868a4ae%5C%22%3EInDrive%20struggled%20to%20crack%20the%20US%20market%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInDrive's%20pricing%20approach%20has%20helped%20it%20expand%20into%2048%20countries%20across%20Latin%20America%2C%20Asia%2C%20and%20Africa.%20In%202025%2C%20it%20was%20the%20second-most%20downloaded%20ride-hailing%20app%20worldwide%2C%20behind%20Uber%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Findrive-secures-no-2-global-140000740.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20provider%3C%2Fa%3E%20Sensor%20Tower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20app%2C%20founded%20in%20Russia%20in%202012%20by%20Arsen%20Tomsky%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findrive-haggling-rideshare-app-enters-us-again-take-uber-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eentered%20the%20US%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%20with%20a%20test%20in%20Florida.%20It%20ended%20the%20test%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%20a%20decision%20Matrosova%20said%20the%20company%20made%20because%20of%20higher%20insurance%20costs%20relative%20to%20other%20countries%20where%20it%20operates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatrosova%20said%20InDrive%20would%20have%20had%20to%20hike%20its%20commission%20rate%20to%20make%20money%20in%20the%20market.%20The%20company%20made%20an%20earlier%20attempt%20to%20crack%20into%20the%20US%20in%202018%2C%20but%20said%20it%20left%20to%20improve%20its%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInDrive%20also%20faced%20a%20competitive%20ride-hailing%20market%20in%20the%20US.%20Uber%20dominated%2076%25%20of%20the%20market%20in%202024%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessofapps.com%2Fdata%2Ftaxi-app-market%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Business%20of%20Apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20the%20US%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EInDrive%20said%20that%20its%20bargaining%20model%20leads%20riders%20to%20use%20its%20service%20more%20often.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfordeconomics.com%2Fresource%2Fthe-economics-of-fare-negotiation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDecember%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Oxford%20Economics%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20InDrive%2C%20found%20that%2064%25%20of%20the%20app's%20customers%20in%20Latin%20America%20took%20more%20rides%20through%20the%20app%20because%20of%20the%20option%20to%20bargain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20that%20it's%20novel%2C%20it's%20actually%20creating%20a%20new%20segment%20in%20the%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Andries%20Smit%2C%20chief%20growth%20officer%20at%20InDrive%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20riders%20and%20drivers%20ultimately%20decide%20prices%2C%20InDrive's%20app%20provides%20some%20guidance.%20If%20a%20rider%20requests%20a%20trip%20in%20a%20busy%20area%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20app%20might%20suggest%20making%20a%20higher%20offer%20in%20order%20to%20match%20with%20a%20driver%2C%20Matrosova%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228142271f-200a-4ab2-a411-09818c4ada36%5C%22%3EInDrive%20is%20also%20growing%20its%20loan%2C%20food%20delivery%20arms%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20ride-hailing%2C%20InDrive%20has%20other%20related%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20a%20growing%20short-term%20loan%20arm%2C%20Smit%20said.%20The%20offering%2C%20which%20the%20company%20first%20tested%20in%20Mexico%20in%202024%2C%20makes%20loans%20of%20up%20to%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20through%20local%20banks%2C%20which%20drivers%20can%20repay%20over%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%2C%20Smit%20said%2C%20is%20to%20help%20drivers%20afford%20unexpected%20expenses%2C%20such%20as%20car%20repairs%20or%20personal%20medical%20expenses%2C%20and%20keep%20them%20on%20the%20app%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20heartbreaking%20when%20we%20see%20drivers%20suddenly%20stop%20driving%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInDrive%20also%20offers%20food%20delivery%20through%20its%20network%20of%20gig-worker%20couriers.%20The%20company%20works%20with%20restaurants%20to%20provide%20delivery%20services%2C%20though%20customers%20still%20have%20to%20order%20through%20the%20restaurants%20themselves.%20That's%20a%20contrast%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-ceo-gets-hundreds-of-emails-on-how-the-company-could-improve-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eservices%20like%20DoorDash%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Uber%20Eats%2C%20where%20users%20can%20place%20food%20orders%20directly%20through%20the%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmit%20said%20he%20sees%20an%20opportunity%20to%20work%20more%20closely%20with%20restaurants%2C%20such%20as%20by%20adding%20menus%20and%20an%20ordering%20function%20to%20the%20app.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20InDrive%20wants%20to%20keep%20its%20model%20transparent%20for%20both%20gig%20workers%20and%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20see%20ourselves%20as%20enablers%20of%20the%20marketplace%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabitter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eabitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20via%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Sign