ha.com%2Fproducts%2Fbeetroot-chukandar%3Fsrsltid%3DAfmBOortbd5gJRtssnSjP7SU7HLnqLKL0uuN0JljNBKbGwjZCdVtvOss%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EmyBageecha%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F344915%2Fhow-to-prepare-natural-holi-colours-at-home-from-beetroot-spinach-turmeric%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeep%20red-purple%20root%20yields%20a%20strong%20natural%20dye%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20juiced.%20This%20juice%20can%20be%20dried%20or%20mixed%20with%20flour%20to%20create%20a%20bold%20rangoli%20pigment.%20Even%20the%20peel%20and%20leafy%20tops%20contain%20colour.%20Since%20beetroot%20is%20edible%2C%20it%20offers%20both%20nutritional%20and%20artistic%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Indigo%20%E2%80%93%20Blue%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndigo%20is%20a%20traditional%20dye%20plant%20that%20has%20been%20used%20for%20centuries%2C%20particularly%20for%20textile%20colouring.%20While%20a%20little%20more%20demanding%20to%20grow%2C%20it%20flourishes%20in%20warm%20climates%20with%20well-drained%20soil%20and%20full%20sunlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20extract%20the%20colour%2C%20the%20leaves%20are%20soaked%20in%20water%20and%20fermented%2C%20triggering%20a%20chemical%20reaction%20that%20releases%20a%20strong%20blue%20pigment.%20This%20process%20can%20be%20a%20fascinating%20natural%20science%20experiment%20for%20older%20children.%20Indigo%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20few%20reliable%20natural%20sources%20of%20true%20blue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E6.%20Spinach%20%E2%80%93%20Green%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpinach%20is%20a%20fast-growing%20leafy%20vegetable%20that%20thrives%20in%20cool%20to%20moderate%20temperatures%20and%20prefers%20partial%20shade.%20The%20leaves%20can%20be%20dried%20and%20crushed%20to%20make%20a%20gentle%20green%20powder%2C%20or%20juiced%20and%20mixed